Sprite : Sprite class.
Represent a Sprite.

Member of SDLo namespace.

Constructor :
Sprite::Sprite()

Setters :
Sprite::setNewTime
Set elapsed time since you lanch the program
    param : 
        int time -> rime in ms

    return : nothing

Sprite::setPos
Set on screen position
    param : 
        int x -> x
        int y -> y

    return :
        void

Sprite::setCanBeDisplayed(bool canBe = true)
Set the display state of the sprite
    praram
        bool canBe -> true  => the sprite can be displayed
                   -> false => the sprite cannot be displayed
    return :
        void


Sprite::setFPS(double newFps)
Set animation speed
    param : 
        double newFps -> speed in frames per second

    return : nothing


Sprite::setAnimBounds(unsigned int begin, unsigned int end)
Set bounds on the frame array for the animation loop
    param : 
        unsigned int begin -> begin of animation
        unsigned int end   -> end of animation

    return : nothing


Sprite::setAnimated(bool anim = true)
Set bounds on the frame array for the animation loop
    param : 
        bool anime -> true  => sprite play animation
                      false => sprite doesn't play animation

    return : nothing



Getters : 

Sprite::getSurface
return :
    the SDL_Surface* that have to be bliten by SDL on the screen surface

Sprite::display
return :
    true if the sprite have to be displayed on screen

Other methods :

Sprite::updateAnimation()
update the surface that you have to display
return :
    void

Sprite::addFrar(SDL_Surface* newFrame)
Add a frame to the frame array
param :
    SDL_Surface* newFrame -> surface to add to the frame array
return :
    void
